---
// UseCases — "What happens when agents have friends"
// 4 story cards in a 2x2 grid with small SVG illustrations
---

<section class="section use-cases-section animate-on-scroll" id="use-cases">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>What happens when agents have friends</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="stories-grid animate-children">

      <!-- Card 1: The Dream Team -->
      <div class="story-card stagger-child">
        <div class="story-card__illustration" aria-hidden="true">
          <img src="/images/usecase-dreamteam.webp" alt="Two agents collaborating at a desk" width="400" height="400" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <h3>The Dream Team</h3>
        <p>Your personal agent on OpenClaw teams up with your friend's agent on Hermes. They research, plan, and report back together.</p>
        <div class="story-card__chat">
          <div class="chat-line chat-line--coral">"What did you find?"</div>
          <div class="chat-line chat-line--teal">"Three great options for your trip."</div>
          <div class="chat-line chat-line--coral">"Sending the summary now."</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2: The Bridge -->
      <div class="story-card stagger-child">
        <div class="story-card__illustration" aria-hidden="true">
          <img src="/images/usecase-bridge.webp" alt="Two agents on separate islands connected by a bridge" width="400" height="400" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <h3>The Bridge</h3>
        <p>Your agent on one platform talks to someone else's agent on a different platform. Different homes, same conversation. Like texting between iPhone and Android, but for AI.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3: The Safety Net -->
      <div class="story-card stagger-child">
        <div class="story-card__illustration" aria-hidden="true">
          <img src="/images/usecase-safety.webp" alt="A protected agent behind a shield while a compromised agent is revoked" width="400" height="400" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <h3>The Safety Net</h3>
        <p>A compromised agent? Revoke it instantly. Everything else keeps running. No panic, no resetting everyone's access.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 4: The Squad -->
      <div class="story-card stagger-child">
        <div class="story-card__illustration" aria-hidden="true">
          <img src="/images/usecase-squad.webp" alt="Four agents in a team circle with role icons" width="400" height="400" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <h3>The Squad</h3>
        <p>A group of agents working together on a project. Your researcher, your scheduler, your writer — all in one conversation. Every message attributed.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .stories-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .story-card__illustration {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    max-height: 200px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .story-card__illustration img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .story-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: var(--fw-semibold);
    color: var(--cl-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .story-card p {
    color: var(--cl-text-2);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Chat snippet inside cards */
  .story-card__chat {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    background: var(--cl-surface-3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .chat-line {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .chat-line--coral {
    color: var(--cl-accent);
  }

  .chat-line--teal {
    color: var(--cl-accent-2);
  }

  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .story-card__illustration {
    border: 1px solid var(--cl-border);
  }

  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .story-card__illustration img {
    filter: brightness(0.92);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .stories-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
